What is
Resilience4j is a Java library that helps build robust, resilient,
and fault-tolerant systems by providing ready-to-use implementations of resilience patterns.

Core Patterns
| Pattern                      | Purpose                                                                                      |
| ---------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| âœ… **Circuit Breaker**        | Prevents cascading failures by breaking the circuit when failures cross a threshold.         |
| ðŸ” **Retry**                 | Automatically retries a failed operation a configurable number of times.                     |
| ðŸ•’ **Time Limiter**          | Sets a time limit for calls. If exceeded, cancels and returns a timeout error.               |
| âš–ï¸ **Rate Limiter**          | Controls the rate of requests per second/minute to prevent overloading services.             |
| ðŸ“¦ **Bulkhead**              | Isolates failures by limiting concurrent calls per resource to avoid system-wide exhaustion. |
| ðŸ§  **Cache**                 | Caches responses to avoid repeated calls to the same resource.                               |
| â± **Scheduler**              | Allows delay and periodic execution of tasks.                                                |
| ðŸ§¾ **Fallback (Decorators)** | Provides alternative response if a call fails (e.g., cached value, default value).           |


